<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1860-06-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1860-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>,
                                    Secretary of State, to Mr. <persName type="to">Boutwell</persName>, Secretary of the Treasury.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1860-06-24"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 24,
                                1860</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your letter of to day,
                                representing that a vessel is fitting out in Philadelphia for the
                                revolutionists in Cuba, and that two men, claiming to have been
                                enlisted for that service, offer information if paid therefor.</p>
                            <p>In reply, I have to state that this Department will cause a
                                reasonable sum to be paid for the information referred to.</p>
                            <p><seg type="margin">[67]</seg> *A copy of your letter has been sent to
                                the Attorney-General. I am, dear sir, yours, &amp;c., &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">George S. Boutwell</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary of the Treasury.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>